same* content — none of them prove the literal spec text \"regardless of whether the message content or model id matches\" by actually varying content or modelId on the retry and still observing 409. The code is correct (it doesn't compare payloads at all), but this specific nuance is **UNTESTED**.\n\n### 10. Web sends only with valid selected model — **CONFORMS**\n- Init from `defaultModelId`: `chat-page.tsx:212-217`, `model-selector.tsx`; tested `model-selector.test.tsx:70`, `chat-page.models.test.tsx:118`.\n- Top-level `modelId` on every send: `transport.ts` `prepareSendMessagesRequest`; tested `transport.test.ts`.\n- Composer stays usable, send disabled until valid: `chat-page.tsx` `modelReadyForSend` gates only the send `PromptInputButton` (`disabled={!modelReadyForSend}`), input textarea is independent state; tested `chat-page.models.test.tsx:103`.\n- `usage.modelId` read exclusively, no legacy fallback: `message-usage.tsx:155-221`; `rg` for `usage.model`/`usage.provider` across `apps/web` returns zero hits.\n\n## Summary\n\n| Verdict | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CONFORMS | 10 / 10 requirements |\n| PARTIAL | 0 |\n| GAP | 0 |\n| Explicit UNTESTED call-outs | 7 (see below) |\n\nEvery requirement is implemented correctly on inspection; nothing contradicts the spec. openapi.json is generated and matches the DTOs exactly (`required: [\"id\",\"source\",\"contextWindowTokens\"]` on `AvailableModelResponse`, `modelId` required on `CreateMessageDto`), and `git diff --exit-code` in CI catches drift.\n\n### Ranked discrepancies worth attention\n\n1. **Highest-impact, outside strict spec text but directly threatens this change's own testability**: `playwright.config.ts` (root) still sets the now-dead `OPENAI_MODEL: \"e2e-mock\"` for the browser-e2e `api` webServer, and **never sets `DEFAULT_MODEL_ID` or `TITLE_GENERATION_MODEL_ID`**. `ConfigModule.forRoot({ envFilePath: '.env.local' })` only fills gaps from `apps/api/.env.local`, which is gitignored (`apps/api/.gitignore:43`)